<subSubSection id="DF9234CCFFB1E058FF564311FD3C9336" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" type="etymology">
<paragraph id="97376747FFB1E058FF564311FE5392A6" blockId="3.[136,1452,1604,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FF564311FEDE927A" bold="true" box="[189,318,1604,1630]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Etymology</emphasis>
—The specific epithet refers to the type-locality, Praia do Bacupari, in the Municipality of Mostardas, 
<collectingRegion id="554CA9A5FFB1E058FF63433DFEBC92A6" box="[136,348,1640,1666]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EF9F27D7FFB1E058FE8C433DFE4F92A6" box="[359,431,1640,1666]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Brazil</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="97376747FFB1E058FF5643D9FD3C9336" blockId="3.[136,1452,1604,2062]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FF5643D9FDA09282" bold="true" box="[189,576,1676,1702]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Suggested Conservation Status</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FDB743D9FCB79282" box="[604,855,1676,1702]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FDB743D9FCB79282" box="[604,855,1676,1702]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
could be considered Critically endangered (CR) according to the 
<bibRefCitation id="F3191AB6FFB1E058FEA343E5FE0092EE" author="IUCN" box="[328,480,1712,1738]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" refId="ref2742" refString="IUCN (2017) Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 13. Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommittee of the IUCN Species Survival Commission. IUCN, Gland and Cambridge. Available from: http: // cmsdocs. s 3. amazonaws. com / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed March 2021)." type="book" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
criteria B1 b(I,ii,iii,iv,v)C1. Its area of occupation (AOO) is 
<quantity id="5070CAA2FFB1E058FB7143E5FAE592E8" box="[1178,1285,1712,1740]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" unit="km" value="8.0">8.000 km</quantity>
² and only two populations of the species were found on sandy soil in the municipality of Mostardas, around salt lagoons, an area that is rapidly being occupied by real estate development.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="DF9234CCFFB1E05FFF564249FDA3956D" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="97376747FFB1E05FFF564249FDA3956D" blockId="3.[136,1452,1604,2062]" lastBlockId="4.[136,1452,158,329]" lastPageId="4" lastPageNumber="244" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FF564249FEDE9312" bold="true" box="[189,318,1820,1846]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Comments</emphasis>
—While 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FE404249FD439312" box="[427,675,1820,1846]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FE404249FD439312" box="[427,675,1820,1846]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to the sandy soils of the dunes, near lagoons in the municipality of Mostardas, Rio Grande do Sul state, 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FD344215FC8C937E" authorityName="Baillon" authorityYear="1864" box="[735,876,1856,1882]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="gnaphalii">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FD344215FC8C937E" box="[735,876,1856,1882]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">C. gnaphalii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in the Pampa’s grasslands, in 
<collectingCountry id="EF9F27D7FFB1E058FF634231FF1A935A" box="[136,250,1892,1918]" name="Argentina" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Argentina</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="EF9F27D7FFB1E058FEEF4231FE86935A" box="[260,358,1892,1918]" name="Uruguay" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Uruguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingRegion id="554CA9A5FFB1E058FE714231FD8A935A" box="[410,618,1892,1918]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
, in Southern 
<collectingCountry id="EF9F27D7FFB1E058FD104231FCA2935A" box="[763,834,1892,1918]" name="Brazil" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, growing mostly in rocky soils. 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FB494231FA73935A" box="[1186,1427,1892,1918]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FB494231FA73935A" box="[1186,1427,1892,1918]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is here classified in 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FEA842DDFD8B9386" authorityName="Pax" authorityYear="1890" baseAuthorityName="Muller Argoviensis" baseAuthorityYear="1873" box="[323,619,1928,1954]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="section" section="Lamprocroton">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FEA842DDFE719386" box="[323,401,1928,1954]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton</emphasis>
sect. 
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FE2042DCFD8B9386" box="[459,619,1929,1954]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Lamprocroton</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
due to the presence of a lepidote indumentum,leaves without petiolar glands, and bifid styles with four terminal tips. The following species occur in the same environment: 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FB5142F9FEA593CE" authority="Croizat (1942: 1)" authorityName="Croizat" authorityPageNumber="1" authorityYear="1942" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lombardianus">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FB5142F9FA4C93E2" box="[1210,1452,1964,1990]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton lombardianus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F3191AB6FFB1E058FF634285FEA593CE" author="Croizat, L." box="[136,325,2000,2026]" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" pagination="1 - 4" refId="ref2554" refString="Croizat, L. (1942) Las especies sudamericanas del genero Croton, I - II. Comunicaciones Botanicas del Museo de Historia Natural de Montevideo 1: 1 - 4." type="journal article" year="1942">Croizat (1942:1)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, which is distinct by having branches predominantly prostrate, serrate leaves and stellate trichomes (vs. ascending branches, entire leaves and stellate-lepidote trichomes in 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FC5842A1FB919C2A" box="[947,1137,2036,2062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FC5842A1FB919C2A" box="[947,1137,2036,2062]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB1E058FB6342A1FA999C2A" authorityName="Croizat" authorityYear="1942" box="[1160,1401,2036,2062]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="3" pageNumber="243" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lombardianus">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB1E058FB6342A1FA999C2A" box="[1160,1401,2036,2062]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="243">Croton lombardianus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was recently recorded to 
<collectingCountry id="EF9F27D7FFB6E05FFE8745CBFE50949C" box="[364,432,158,184]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Brazil</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="F3191AB6FFB6E05FFE3345CBFD24949C" author="Valduga, E. &amp; Molz, M. &amp; Cordeiro, I. &amp; Iganci, J." box="[472,708,158,184]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="189 - 194" refId="ref3709" refString="Valduga, E., Molz, M., Cordeiro, I. &amp; Iganci, J. (2021) Novelties in Croton (Euphorbiaceae) from southern South America. Phytotaxa 496: 189 - 194. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 496.2.8" type="journal article" year="2021">
Valduga 
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB6E05FFDD145CAFD91949C" box="[570,625,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">et al.</emphasis>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
. 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB6E05FFD2545CAFB4D949D" authority="Linnaeus (1759: 1275)" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityPageNumber="1275" authorityYear="1759" box="[718,1197,158,185]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="glandulosus">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB6E05FFD2545CAFC4A949C" box="[718,938,158,185]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Croton glandulosus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F3191AB6FFB6E05FFC5B45CBFB4D949D" author="Linnaeus, C." box="[944,1197,158,185]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="825 - 1384" refId="ref2993" refString="Linnaeus, C. (1759) Systema Naturae ed. 10, 2. Laurentius Salvius, Stockholm, pp. 825 - 1384." type="book chapter" year="1759">Linnaeus (1759: 1275)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is distinguished by the serrate leaves and stipitate glands at the base of the leaf blade, or at the apex of the petiole (vs. entire leaves without glands in 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB6E05FFF1F45B2FE529524" box="[244,434,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB6E05FFF1F45B2FE529524" box="[244,434,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB6E05FFE2245B2FC6A9525" authority="Baillon (1864: 358)" authorityName="Baillon" authorityPageNumber="358" authorityYear="1864" box="[457,906,230,257]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="helichrysum">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB6E05FFE2245B2FD479524" box="[457,679,230,257]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Croton helichrysum</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F3191AB6FFB6E05FFD4645B3FC6A9525" author="Baillon, H. E." box="[685,906,230,257]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="257 - 377" refId="ref2413" refString="Baillon, H. E. (1864) Species Euphorbiacearum. Euphorbiacees Americaines. Premiere partie: Amerique austro-orientale. Adansonia 4: 257 - 377." type="journal article" year="1864">Baillon (1864: 358)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the spatulate leaves (vs. elliptic leaves in 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB6E05FFF1A445EFE4E9500" box="[241,430,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB6E05FFF1A445EFE4E9500" box="[241,430,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB6E05FFE06445EFC679500" authority="Lamarck (1786: 211)" authorityName="Lamarck" authorityPageNumber="211" authorityYear="1786" box="[493,903,266,293]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="lanatus">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB6E05FFE06445EFD749500" box="[493,660,266,293]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">Croton lanatus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="F3191AB6FFB6E05FFD70445FFC679500" author="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de" box="[667,903,266,292]" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" pagination="1 - 400" refId="ref2829" refString="Lamarck, J. B. A. P. M. de (1786) Encyclopedie Methodique, Botanique 2 (1). Panckoucke, Paris &amp; Plomteux, Liege, pp. 1 - 400." type="book chapter" year="1786">Lamarck (1786: 211)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
presents sessile glands at the base of the leaf (vs. leaf glands absent in 
<taxonomicName id="50881CC4FFB6E05FFE9F447AFDD2956C" box="[372,562,302,329]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Croton" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="4" pageNumber="244" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="bacupariensis">
<emphasis id="A5FCBB55FFB6E05FFE9F447AFDD2956C" box="[372,562,302,329]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="244">C. bacupariensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
